<br>
My personal opinion is that GM events get advertised too much.  The GMs/quest troupe should keep a somewhat lower profile, and just run events for smaller numbers of players who might actually try to follow through with whatever quest or task they are presented with.  Back around the Velious release, some of my guildmates and I ended up being given a set of quests to complete by a GM, who we would meet every few days in Mistmoore.  It was very cool, even though nothing substantial came of it.  Some roleplaying was required to make it fun, and because we were able to do it as a guild, it was more memorable afterwards.  Doing huge events to cater to the masses is NOT memorable, and all it does is piss people off.<br>
<br>
 <p>Somberlain Wayfaerer<BR>
Wanderer of Druzzil Ro<BR>
Guild Leader of the Justice Knights<BR>
<a href="http://www.geocities.com/justiceknights/jk.html">www.geocities.com/justiceknights</a> <BR>
