<br>
Another problem I have seen is timing.  Gm chars show up, word gets passed around, and an hour later with 100 people watching, something happens.<br>
<br>
As alternatives, I'd ask, why don't we have ongoing, invulnerable chars, so that many more people have a chance to interact with them?<br>
<br>
Also, why not have the npc's show up, do their business, and leave.  Why wait for 12 guilds to arrive?<br>
<br>
At this point it should be obvious that npc's which pass the turing test are not really viable opponents.  So their purpose must be more related to infotainment.<br>
<br>
