<br>
Also, I remember a GM event myself in OT where the some of the dragoons were GM controlled.  I love flirting with the dragoons, but normally they just stand there doing nothing.  The only response I ever got out of them was when General V'Deers accused me of trying to buy friends for giving him a cookie!  It was a big thrill to have them respond to my flirtations for once, hehe.  (Then all the other dark elf ladies started flirting with them too!)    <br>
<br>
So loot is not always important, so long as the event is enjoyable.  <br>
